text: Wyeth is an unincorporated community in Andrew County, in the U.S. state of Missouri. ==History== An old variant name was Rush, after Peter Rush, a local landowner. A post office called Rush was established in 1890, the name was changed into Wyeth in 1904, and the post office closed in 1905. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Andrew County, Missouri Category:Unincorporated communities in Missouri
title: Wyeth, Missouri
